    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The forkchoice `getHead()` does not seem right. Previously we do `syncChanges()` to apply weight change for each node when we call `getHead()` and the head can move forward thanks to that, now we don't do any weight changing actions when we call `getHead()`. Refer to https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/v0.11.0/packages/lodestar/src/chain/forkChoice/arrayDag/lmdGhost.ts#L335\r\n\r\nCurrently when we add a block, I think it'll all have 0 weight by default and the head moves forward solely based on parent-child relationship until it reaches an orphaned block. At that time, it'll try to resolve best child/best descendant based on `maybeUpdateBestChildAndDescendant` and it'll finally come to tie break condition where it based on hex root comparison (bc most of blocks have 0 weight) and then it gets stuck there.",
